==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Siphonobranchiata
<hw>Si`pho*no*bran`chi*a"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL. See <er>Siphon</er>, and <er>Branchia</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A tribe of gastropods having the mantle border,
on one or both sides, prolonged in the form of a spout through which
water enters the gill cavity. The shell itself is not always
siphonostomatous in this group.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1346 --></p>

<p><ent>Siphonobranchiate</ent>⟦br⟧
